cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper presents a method for training self-binarizing neural networks, which involves optimizing the weights and activations of the network to become binary. This topic is closely related to neural network optimization (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and natural language processing (cs.CL) as binary networks have been shown to be useful in these areas. Additionally, the paper presents results on multiple benchmark datasets, which suggests that it could also be relevant to the sub-categories of computer vision and machine learning that focus on classification tasks.
